<p>A healthcare worker earning $60,000 per year in Minnesota on a bi-weekly schedule ($2,308 gross per check) pays: $140 in Minnesota income tax (6.8% marginal bracket), $143 in Social Security (6.2%), $33 in Medicare (1.45%) -- net take-home approximately $1,791 per paycheck.</p>

